1996-07-06
»»»»»»»»»»
 This  release  is  called  1.14,  but  it is not finished.  Because I have
failed  - big time - to release new upgrades, I have decided to release the
source  code in the hope that somebody is willing to take over Textread.  I
still  consider  this  program  to be very good, I use it every day myself.
Sure,  some  things  are  lacking, but the fact is that it has everything I
need.   That,  and  the fact that it is written completly in assembler, are
the reasons why I don't have any motivation to continue to improve it.

 So  instead  of letting more time pass, my hope is that somebody out there
can  clean  up  the  source,  fix  the  bugs and release a new version.  Or
perhaps  just  keep  the  good  parts and begin from scratch (may I suggest
another language than assembler?).

 To  those  who  have sent be bugreports, ideas and comments and especially
those  of  you  who  have  paid  the shareware fee...  What can I say?  I'm
sorry.   If  is wasn't for you I would have stopped developing this program
years ago.

 A  big "thank you!" must also go to Olivier ANH for the frensh translation
of  the  documentation.   Unfortunately,  I lost your address and have been
unable  to  contact you.  I hope your work was not in vain, but can be used
in a futute version of Textread.

 Have a wonderful life, and may God bless you all.
   Martin Blom

PS.   If  somebody decides to continue the program, would you be so kind to
contact me first?  Thank you!  DS.


@ENDNODE

